  "description": "One of the most popular queries on Wolfram&#124;Alpha is for definite integrals. So we&#8217;re especially excited to announce that Step-by-step solutions for these are now available! The general method used to find the steps for definite integrals is to tap into the already existing “Show steps” functionality for indefinite integration, and then to use the fundamental [&#8230;]",
  "content:encoded": "<p>One of the most popular queries on Wolfram|Alpha is for <a href=\"http://www.wolframalpha.com/input/?i=definite+integrals\">definite integrals</a>. So we&#8217;re especially excited to announce that Step-by-step solutions for these are now available! The general method used to find the steps for definite integrals is to tap into the already existing “Show steps” functionality for indefinite integration, and then to use the fundamental theorem of calculus.<span id=\"more-28738\"></span></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.wolframalpha.com/input/?i=integrate+Sin[x]^2+Cos[x]+from+0+to+pi%2F2\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-28811\" title=\"Domain is split and the integral is evaluated separately over each domain\" src=\"https://content.wolfram.com/uploads/sites/35/2014/09/1-sbs.png\" alt=\"Domain is split and the integral is evaluated separately over each domain\" width=\"505\" height=\"562\" srcset=\"https://content.wolfram.com/uploads/sites/35/2014/09/1-sbs.png 505w, https://content.wolfram.com/uploads/sites/35/2014/09/1-sbs-269x300.png 269w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 505px) 100vw, 505px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Now you may think it was trivial to add this functionality given that indefinite integrals already have steps, but there are many tricky cases to consider: before we even begin to integrate, the continuity of the function is examined. If there are discontinuities in the integration domain, the domain is split and the integral is evaluated separately over each domain.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.wolframalpha.com/input/?i=integrate+arccot%28x%29+from+-1+to+2\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-28813\" title=\"Domain split and integral evaluated separately\" src=\"https://content.wolfram.com/uploads/sites/35/2014/09/2-sbs-05.png\" alt=\"Domain split and integral evaluated separately\" width=\"505\" height=\"590\" srcset=\"https://content.wolfram.com/uploads/sites/35/2014/09/2-sbs-05.png 505w, https://content.wolfram.com/uploads/sites/35/2014/09/2-sbs-05-256x300.png 256w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 505px) 100vw, 505px\" /></a></p>\n<p>We must determine if the integral is proper or improper.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.wolframalpha.com/input/?i=integrate+1%2Fsqrt%28x%29+from+0+to+1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-28814\" title=\"Integral proper or improper\" src=\"https://content.wolfram.com/uploads/sites/35/2014/09/3-sbs.png\" alt=\"Integral proper or improper\" width=\"505\" height=\"648\" srcset=\"https://content.wolfram.com/uploads/sites/35/2014/09/3-sbs.png 505w, https://content.wolfram.com/uploads/sites/35/2014/09/3-sbs-233x300.png 233w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 505px) 100vw, 505px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Absolute values need to be handled carefully.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.wolframalpha.com/input/?i=integrate+|sin%28x%29|+from+0+to+2pi\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-28815\" title=\"Absolute values handled carefully\" src=\"https://content.wolfram.com/uploads/sites/35/2014/09/4-sbs.png\" alt=\"Absolute values handled carefully\" width=\"505\" height=\"459\" srcset=\"https://content.wolfram.com/uploads/sites/35/2014/09/4-sbs.png 505w, https://content.wolfram.com/uploads/sites/35/2014/09/4-sbs-300x272.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 505px) 100vw, 505px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Symmetries can be exploited.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.wolframalpha.com/input/?i=integrate+1%2F%28x^2+%2B+1%29+from+-infinity+to+infinity\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-28816\" title=\"Symmetries exploited\" src=\"https://content.wolfram.com/uploads/sites/35/2014/09/5-sbs.png\" alt=\"Symmetries exploited\" width=\"505\" height=\"700\" srcset=\"https://content.wolfram.com/uploads/sites/35/2014/09/5-sbs.png 505w, https://content.wolfram.com/uploads/sites/35/2014/09/5-sbs-216x300.png 216w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 505px) 100vw, 505px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Simplification of radicals and logarithms must be done very carefully.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.wolframalpha.com/input/?i=integrate+sqrt%289t^4+%2B+4t^2%29+from+-1+to+1\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-28817\" title=\"Simplification of algorithms and logarithms handled carefully\" src=\"https://content.wolfram.com/uploads/sites/35/2014/09/6-sbs-02.png\" alt=\"Simplification of algorithms and logarithms handled carefully\" width=\"505\" height=\"590\" srcset=\"https://content.wolfram.com/uploads/sites/35/2014/09/6-sbs-02.png 505w, https://content.wolfram.com/uploads/sites/35/2014/09/6-sbs-02-256x300.png 256w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 505px) 100vw, 505px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Finally, the fundamental theorem of calculus requires that the antiderivative is continuous over the integration domain (see <a href=\"http://blog.wolfram.com/2008/01/19/mathematica-and-the-fundamental-theorem-of-calculus/\">this blog post</a> for more information). Therefore, we need to be careful when finding the indefinite integral, and always ensure the result will be continuous. One way to do this is to detect when we will have a discontinuous antiderivative and split the integration domain up.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.wolframalpha.com/input/?i=integrate+1%2F%28cos%28x%29+%2B+2%29+from+0+to+3pi%2F2\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-28818\" title=\"Detect a discontinuous antiderivative and split the integration domain up\" src=\"https://content.wolfram.com/uploads/sites/35/2014/09/7-sbs-02.png\" alt=\"Detect a discontinuous antiderivative and split the integration domain up\" width=\"505\" height=\"590\" srcset=\"https://content.wolfram.com/uploads/sites/35/2014/09/7-sbs-02.png 505w, https://content.wolfram.com/uploads/sites/35/2014/09/7-sbs-02-256x300.png 256w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 505px) 100vw, 505px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Integration is an extremely nontrivial problem, so we hope these Step-by-step solutions will help you learn how they can be done. Be sure to check out Step-by-step solutions for <a href=\"http://www.wolframalpha.com/examples/StepByStepSolutions.html\">other topics</a> too.</p>\n",
